<br>
Base HP = 4200<br>
ND3 = +10%<br>
PE = +2%<br>
Planar Dura = +25%<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Post AA HP = 4200 * 1.37 = 5754</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Now let's add buffs....</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Brells = 200<br>
PoP Aego Upgrade = 1500<br>
Focus Upgrade = 520<br>
STA Buff = 200*1.37 = 274<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Buffed HP = 5754 + 200 + 1500 + 520 + 274 = 8248</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> How about level HP? Maybe 25 hp per level? <br>
What about Increased STA bonus? Maybe 5/sta at 65?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Level HP = 125*1.37 = 171<br>
STA Bonus HP = 305*1.37 = 418<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Theoretical Buffed HP = 8837</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
That would be one insane HP number for a monk, hell for any class and it wouldn't even be the maximum. Current items available, allow a monk to hit nearly 4600 unbuffed HP without accounting for AA points. Just suppose for a moment, that one of the monks in FoH, Afterlife or something managed to hit that 4600 number after getting a bit of PoP gear. Some of them aren't terribly far away as is. They'd have an additional 400*1.37 = 548hp, pushing the total to a staggering <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 9395 Fully raid buffed HP</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> if all of this came to pass.<br>
<br>
I'm very intersted to see how things finally come out with this stuff. I'd really like to know if the AA points use the same point pool and if these lvls/abilities will work anywhere in EQ too. Only time will tell i suppose. <p><img src="http://www.adventurersanon.com/images/sigs/axiss_sig.gif"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10004">Magelo Profile</a>
